children.subject: You can't be enrolled in "either discussion or lecture" without being enrolled in both.

If you're 15th on the lecture waitlist, you're fine. Discussion enrollment doesn't matter; just be enrolled in either discussion or lecture and you're fine.

TL;DR don't worry

history.content:
There is a good chance but it is not at all guaranteed.  Since Cogsci 131 is being offered now in Fall 16 and fulfills that same requirement for the cogsci major, it would have been a good idea to take that course if you couldn't get into 188 in fall.

I really hope it works out for you.

I'm a CogSci major and need to take CS 188 in Spring - my final semester - in order to graduate. There are no other courses that would fulfill the requirement; otherwise, I wouldn't be cluttering up piazza with a post like this.

I'm 15th on the lecture waitlist but my discussion is now fully enrolled (someone who's already enrolled in the lecture just took the last spot to make it 35/35). I'm not entirely sure that I'm first on my discussion's waitlist, but I'm surely not far from it. Is there enough turnover in 188 that I'm likely to get in?
